.TH "aer_get_device_error_info" 9 "aer_get_device_error_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aer_get_device_error_info \- read error status from dev and store it to info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" aer_get_device_error_info
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct aer_err_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to the device expected to have a error record
.IP "info" 12
pointer to structure to store the error record
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 1 on success, 0 on error.

Note that \fIinfo\fP is reused among all error devices. Clear fields properly.
